    "body": "See [this](https://forum.generic-mapping-tools.org/t/how-to-set-datadir-and-see-all-environment-variables/2994) forum post for background.\r\n\r\nA path set with `$GMT_DATADIR` will not be set in ``gmt --show-datadir``. `gmt set DIR_DATA=/data` will. According to the [cookbook](https://docs.generic-mapping-tools.org/dev/cookbook/features.html#directory-parameters) both of these should work, and `DIR_DATA` will [override](https://docs.generic-mapping-tools.org/dev/gmt.conf.html#term-DIR_DATA) the `$GMT_DATADIR` environment variable.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ gmt --show-datadir\r\nNot set\r\n$ GMT_DATADIR=/data\r\n$ echo $GMT_DATADIR\r\n/data\r\n$ gmt --show-datadir\r\nNot set\r\n$ gmt set DIR_DATA=/data\r\n$ gmt --show-datadir\r\n/data\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo, ``gmt --show-datadir`` should report the path set by `$GMT_DATADIR`, but it does not.",
